quran[34]{c,v,t}:
  56,17,"They will be served in rounds by Immortal boys"
  56,18,"with bowls and jugs and a goblet of pure wine,"
  56,19,"from which they will neither suffer headache, nor will they be intoxicated,"
  56,20,"and with fruits of their choice,"
  56,21,"and the meat of birds that they desire."
  56,22,"And (for them there will be) houris, having lovely big eyes,"
  56,23,"all (neat and clean) like a hidden pearl,"
  56,24,"as a reward for what they used to do."
  56,25,"They will hear neither an absurd talk therein, nor something leading to sin,"
  56,26,"but the words of salam, salam (as greetings)."
  56,27,"As for the People of the Right, how (lucky) are the People of the Right!"
  56,28,"(They will be) amid lote-trees with no horns,"
  56,29,"and the trees of tall, (banana, or a fragrant tree) having layers one upon the other,"
  56,30,"and a shade, spread all over,"
  56,31,"and water, poured forth,"
  56,32,"and a lot of fruits"
  56,33,"neither interrupted (in any season), nor prohibited,"
  56,34,"and mattresses of high quality."
  56,35,"Surely We have created those (females) a fresh creation,"
  56,36,"and have made them virgins,"
  56,37,"amorous to their husbands, matching them in age,"
  56,38,"for the People of the Right,"
  56,39,"(comprising) many from the earlier generations,"
  56,40,"and many from the later ones."
  56,41,"As for the People of the Left, How (wretched) are the People of the Left!"
  56,42,"(They will be) in burning wind and boiling water,"
  56,43,"and in a shade of black smoke,"
  56,44,"] neither cool nor graceful."
  56,45,"They were before that indulged in luxuries,"
  56,46,"and used to persist in major sins,"
  56,47,"and used to say, "Is it that when we die and become dust-is it that we will be raised again,"
  56,48,"and our ancient fathers as well?""
  56,49,"Say, "All the earlier and the later ones"
  56,50,"will be gathered together for a fixed time of a specified Day."